    "updated_at": "2023-09-04T14:45:40Z",
    "body": "See https://github.com/starship/starship/pull/4550 (waiting for review) which does not allow you to specify a complete new fomat, but style and symbol and allows you to do regex replacements within the name. So while you could probably not end up with `'[!!! PRODUCTION !!!](red) $cluster'` but with something like of `'[!!! PRODUCTION $cluster !!!](red)` -> all red, not only the `!!! Prod !!!` part. E.g. via setting `context_pattern` to your regex, `context_alias` to `!!! PRODUCTION $cluster !!!` and `style = red`.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
